---
description: "Rules for wiring UI behavior and state without coupling to gameplay"
alwaysApply: false
---

## Authority & Data Flow (MANDATORY)

- UI emits intent only
- Server or authoritative controller decides outcomes
- UI updates only from confirmed state

UI must NEVER:
- assume success
- mutate authoritative state
- talk directly to datastores

---

## Menu Behavior Contract (TYPE 2)

Menus may own:
- open/close lifecycle
- focus handling (Dimmer)
- local selection state (e.g., selected item id)

Menus must NEVER:
- resolve purchases
- equip items
- grant rewards
- save data

Required behavior shape:
- OpenMenu(menuId)
- CloseMenu(menuId)
- EmitIntent(action, payload)
- RenderFromState(state)

---

## Button Binding Rules

Buttons:
- play feedback animations
- emit intent on activation

Buttons must NOT:
- branch logic
- resolve outcomes
- change game state

---

## Interactive UI Behavior (TYPE 3)

Interactive UI:
- is created once and reused
- is driven by a state machine
- animates on state entry/exit only

Rules:
- animations are state-bound
- no free-running animations
- no UI rebuilds per state

State is represented by:
- visibility
- color
- gradients
- values
- ZIndex / transparency

---

## No Variant Rebuild Rule (MANDATORY)

Do NOT create separate UI variants per state.

Use:
- visibility toggles
- recolors
- texture swaps
- gradient changes
